flowRoot.flowPara: OS logo shown at the bottom
Vendor logo position is specified by the UEFI spec.

Vendor logo isn't shown at this step, because it interferes with the password field. This unfortunately means that the vendor logo disappears and then appears again. However, this style of disk encryption isn't ideal anyway, and we should work towards better solutions. Also, the vendor logo is expected to be shown, partly due to the UEFI spec (which even allows organisations to replace it with their own logo.
Styling of password entry is somewhat unique, owing to the fact that this is a non-standard environment - solid black background, and so on.

Live images are a bit special - there's no way for users to boot into the boot menu. People sometimes need access to this in order to edit the boot command, which is required to make some hardware work. Therefore, we show a hint and a timeout in this case.
